# === finding-02d8a986-4f6b-4608-82d4-dda99438687d ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-02d8a986-4f6b-4608-82d4-dda99438687d> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-27T17:08:35.009226Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Google Q4 2025 earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "91ea36f6-9248-4f8f-a35c-65603e275bb8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:08:35.009060+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here are the complete findings for Alphabet/Google's Q4 2025 earnings (reported February 4, 2026):\n\n---\n\n## Alphabet Q4 2025 Earnings — Key Findings\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & Growth\n- **Q4 Revenue: $113.83B** (+18% YoY vs. $96.5B in Q4 2024)\n- **Full-Year 2025: $402.84B** — first time exceeding $400B in company history\n- Net Income: $34.46B (+30% YoY)\n\n### 2. EPS vs. Estimates\n- **EPS: $2.82 actual vs. $2.61–$2.64 estimated** (~8% beat)\n- Revenue beat by ~$2.7B (~2.4% above consensus)\n\n### 3. Google Search & Advertising\n- **Total Ad Revenue: $82.28B** (+13.5% YoY)\n- **Google Search: $63.1B** (+17% YoY) — record quarter\n- YouTube Ads: $11.38B (+8.7% YoY, slowed due to lapping 2024 election spending)\n- Network revenue: $7.83B (-1.5% YoY)\n\n### 4. Google Cloud\n- **Revenue: $17.7B (+48% YoY)** — fastest-growing major hyperscaler\n- vs. AWS: ~$28.8B (+18%), Azure: ~25% growth\n- Cloud backlog: $240B (+55% sequential); annual run rate >$70B\n\n### 5. Other Bets\n- Revenue: $370M (-7.5% YoY); Operating loss: -$3.61B (tripled)\n- Loss driven by $2.1B Waymo SBC charge; Waymo hit 20M+ lifetime trips, 400K+ weekly rides\n\n### 6. AI / Gemini\n- Gemini: **750M MAUs**, 8M+ enterprise seats, 10B+ tokens/min\n- Serving costs down **78% over 2025**\n- CEO Pichai: company will be \"supply constrained\" throughout 2026\n\n### 7. Capex — The Market Mover\n- Q4 2025 actual: $27.9B; FY 2025: $91.4B\n- **FY 2026 guidance: $175–185B** (vs. Street est. of ~$119.5B — shocked analysts by $55–65B)\n\n### 8. Stock Reaction\n- Stock near all-time high (~$343) before earnings\n- Initial after-hours pop → reversed sharply on capex guidance → **-7% to -10% in the following week** (~$302–313)\n\n### 9. Analyst Consensus\n- 60 Buy / 7 Hold / 0 Sell (67 analysts)\n- Median price target: ~$380–$387; Goldman/RBC/Scotiabank at $400, JPM at $395\n- Bears focused on capex compression of free cash flow; bulls focused on cloud/AI long-term ROI\n\n---\n\nNotes saved to `google_q4_2025_earnings.md` (pending write permission). The dominant narrative: **beat on every core metric, but the $175–185B capex \"shock\" dominated sentiment** and drove the stock lower despite the operational outperformance." ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "b3074ae8-ae6b-4a38-9a23-9d0821072823" ;
