# === finding-1edfa3aa-7b16-4223-9c0f-843cdbd0f23c ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-1edfa3aa-7b16-4223-9c0f-843cdbd0f23c> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-27T17:26:17.305463Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Write cross-company correlations\",\"coder\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "91ea36f6-9248-4f8f-a35c-65603e275bb8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:26:17.305314+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "The write requires your permission. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp/swarm-parallel-stocks/analysis/correlations.md`.\n\nThe file I've prepared identifies **9 shared patterns** and **5 divergences** across all four companies and three sectors:\n\n**Key patterns found:**\n1. Universal revenue beats, but stock reactions driven by capex shock severity (not operational results)\n2. Combined ~$495–640B hyperscaler capex — all using identical \"supply-constrained\" language\n3. All four companies avoided explicit AI revenue disclosure (Amazon closest with $10B+ Trainium ARR)\n4. AWS ($244B) and Google Cloud ($240B) backlogs are nearly identical — a striking convergence\n5. All three hyperscalers deployed custom silicon as a shared NVIDIA hedge (TPU Ironwood, Trainium3, Maia 200)\n6. TSMC is the single chokepoint for every demand vector: Apple iPhone, NVIDIA Blackwell, Google TPU, Amazon Trainium, Broadcom XPU, Micron HBM\n7. Both Alphabet and Amazon had excellent ad results that were completely ignored due to capex shock\n8. The optimization cycle is definitively over; the AI spending cycle has fully begun\n\n**Key divergences:**\n- Apple's structurally different position (no cloud, net beneficiary not net spender)\n- Margin structures: Microsoft 43% cloud margins vs. Google Cloud 20% (still maturing)\n- Microsoft's gradual capex telegraphing vs. Amazon/Alphabet's abrupt shock explains stock reaction asymmetry\n- The Anthropic axis: both Amazon and Google are major backers of the same AI lab\n- Free cash flow reckoning deferred to 2027–2028 depreciation wave" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "564fed01-0c3c-446c-9d37-c27a1d5fdab5" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The write requires your permission. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp/swarm-parallel-stocks/analysis/correlations.md`.\n\nThe file I've prepared identifies **9 shared patterns** and **5 divergences** across all four companies and three sectors:\n\n**Key patterns found:**\n1. Universal revenue beats, but stock reactions driven by capex shock severity (not operational results)\n2. Combined ~$495–640B hyperscaler capex — all using identical \"supply-constrained\" language\n3. All four companies avoided explicit AI revenue disclosure (Amazon closest with $10B+ Trainium ARR)\n4. AWS ($244B) and Google Cloud ($240B) backlogs are nearly identical — a striking convergence\n5. All three hyperscalers deployed custom silicon as a shared NVIDIA hedge (TPU Ironwood, Trainium3, Maia 200)\n6. TSMC is the single chokepoint for every demand vector: Apple iPhone, NVIDIA Blackwell, Google TPU, Amazon Trainium, Broadcom XPU, Micron HBM\n7. Both Alphabet and Amazon had excellent ad results that were completely ignored due to capex shock\n8. The optimization cycle is definitively over; the AI spending cycle has fully begun\n\n**Key divergences:**\n- Apple's structurally different position (no cloud, net beneficiary not net spender)\n- Margin structures: Microsoft 43% cloud margins vs. Google Cloud 20% (still maturing)\n- Microsoft's gradual capex telegraphing vs. Amazon/Alphabet's abrupt shock explains stock reaction asymmetry\n- The Anthropic axis: both Amazon and Google are major backers of the same AI lab\n- Free cash flow reckoning deferred to 2027–2028 depreciation wave" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The write requires your permission. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp/swarm-parallel-stocks/" ;
	a <https://schema.org/SemanticMemory> .


