	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:04:30.651923+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is a complete summary of Amazon's Q4 2025 earnings findings:\n\n---\n\n## Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings — Research Summary\n**Reported: February 5, 2026**\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & Growth\n- **$213.4B** (+14% YoY) vs. estimate of $211.3B — **beat**\n\n### 2. EPS\n- **$1.95** reported vs. **$1.97** estimated — **slight miss**\n\n### 3. AWS Revenue & Growth\n- **$35.6B** (+24% YoY) vs. estimate of $34.9B — **beat**\n- Fastest AWS growth in 13 quarters; annualized run rate ~$142B\n- AWS order backlog: **$244B** (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ)\n\n### 4. AWS Operating Income & Margin\n- **$12.47B** operating income (beat $11.91B estimate)\n- **~35% operating margin** (up from 34.6% in Q3)\n\n### 5. E-Commerce Segments\n- **North America**: $127.1B (+10% YoY)\n- **International**: $50.7B (+17% YoY; +11% constant currency)\n\n### 6. Advertising Revenue\n- **$21.3B** (+23% YoY)\n\n### 7. AI Services Commentary\n- **Bedrock** used by 100,000+ companies\n- **Trainium2**: 1.4M chips deployed, fully subscribed; powers Project Rainier (500K+ chip cluster used by Anthropic for Claude training)\n- **Trainium + Graviton** combined ARR: $10B+, growing triple-digits YoY\n- **Trainium3**: In production; nearly all supply committed by mid-2026\n- **Trainium4**: Expected 2027 — 6x FP4 compute vs. T3\n\n### 8. Capital Expenditure\n- **2026 CapEx: ~$200B** vs. analyst estimate of $146.6B (+56% shock)\n- Focus: AI infrastructure, custom chips, robotics, Project Kuiper satellites\n- Amazon issued EUR 14.5B bond to fund AI buildout\n\n### 9. Forward Guidance (Q1 2026)\n- Revenue: **$173.5B–$178.5B** (vs. estimate $175.2B — in-line)\n- Operating income: **$16.5B–$21.5B**\n- ~180 bps FX tailwind\n\n### 10. Stock Reaction\n- **After-hours**: -11%\n- **Next day close**: -8%\n- **Subsequent weeks**: Still ~15% below pre-announcement levels\n- Cause: $200B capex shock overshadowed all operational beats\n\n### 11. Analyst Reactions\n- **Consensus**: Bullish; avg price target ~$280.47\n- **UBS**: Raised 4Q25–4Q27 CapEx estimates to $344B; calls AMZN \"a coiled spring\" projecting ~$20B incremental FCF by 2028\n- **Morningstar**: \"$200B capex overshadows good results\"; limits margin expansion for years\n- **General tone**: Mixed — strong AWS/revenue beats, but EPS miss and capex surprise hit the stock\n\n---\n\nThe file write was blocked by permissions. The notes above represent the complete structured findings. The single dominant narrative from this earnings: **operationally strong beat across the board, but the $200B capex plan for 2026 was the story** — it spooked markets while bulls argue it positions AWS to double revenue by 2028.\n\nSources:\n- [Amazon IR Official Release](https://ir.aboutamazon.com/news-release/news-release-details/2026/Amazon-com-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Results/)\n- [CNBC Q4 Earnings Report](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Futurum Group: AWS +24% Amid $200B Capex](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/amazon-q4-fy-2025-revenue-beat-aws-24-amid-200b-capex-plan/)\n- [Investing.com: Revenue +14%, AWS +24%](https://www.investing.com/news/company-news/amazon-q4-2025-slides-revenue-jumps-14-aws-growth-accelerates-to-24-93CH-4489269)\n- [Morningstar: $200B Capex Overshadows Results](https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/amazon-earnings-guidance-200-billion-capital-expenditure-2026-overshadows-good-results)\n- [Yahoo Finance: Stock Falls on Capex](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/amazon-stock-slides-9-2026-213833761.html)\n- [Motley Fool Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [SEC Official Filing](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1018724/000101872426000002/amzn-20251231xex991.htm)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "c3dda1cb-74df-4314-955b-a5c60c7a3941" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is a complete summary of Amazon's Q4 2025 earnings findings:\n\n---\n\n## Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings — Research Summary\n**Reported: February 5, 2026**\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & Growth\n- **$213.4B** (+14% YoY) vs. estimate of $211.3B — **beat**\n\n### 2. EPS\n- **$1.95** reported vs. **$1.97** estimated — **slight miss**\n\n### 3. AWS Revenue & Growth\n- **$35.6B** (+24% YoY) vs. estimate of $34.9B — **beat**\n- Fastest AWS growth in 13 quarters; annualized run rate ~$142B\n- AWS order backlog: **$244B** (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ)\n\n### 4. AWS Operating Income & Margin\n- **$12.47B** operating income (beat $11.91B estimate)\n- **~35% operating margin** (up from 34.6% in Q3)\n\n### 5. E-Commerce Segments\n- **North America**: $127.1B (+10% YoY)\n- **International**: $50.7B (+17% YoY; +11% constant currency)\n\n### 6. Advertising Revenue\n- **$21.3B** (+23% YoY)\n\n### 7. AI Services Commentary\n- **Bedrock** used by 100,000+ companies\n- **Trainium2**: 1.4M chips deployed, fully subscribed; powers Project Rainier (500K+ chip cluster used by Anthropic for Claude training)\n- **Trainium + Graviton** combined ARR: $10B+, growing triple-digits YoY\n- **Trainium3**: In production; nearly all supply committed by mid-2026\n- **Trainium4**: Expected 2027 — 6x FP4 compute vs. T3\n\n### 8. Capital Expenditure\n- **2026 CapEx: ~$200B** vs. analyst estimate of $146.6B (+56% shock)\n- Focus: AI infrastructure, custom chips, robotics, Project Kuiper satellites\n- Amazon issued EUR 14.5B bond to fund AI buildout\n\n### 9. Forward Guidance (Q1 2026)\n- Revenue: **$173.5B–$178.5B** (vs. estimate $175.2B — in-line)\n- Operating income: **$16.5B–$21.5B**\n- ~180 bps FX tailwind\n\n### 10. Stock Reaction\n- **After-hours**: -11%\n- **Next day close**: -8%\n- **Subsequent weeks**: Still ~15% below pre-announcement levels\n- Cause: $200B capex shock overshadowed all operational beats\n\n### 11. Analyst Reactions\n- **Consensus**: Bullish; avg price target ~$280.47\n- **UBS**: Raised 4Q25–4Q27 CapEx estimates to $344B; calls AMZN \"a coiled spring\" projecting ~$20B incremental FCF by 2028\n- **Morningstar**: \"$200B capex overshadows good results\"; limits margin expansion for years\n- **General tone**: Mixed — strong AWS/revenue beats, but EPS miss and capex surprise hit the stock\n\n---\n\nThe file write was blocked by permissions. The notes above represent the complete structured findings. The single dominant narrative from this earnings: **operationally strong beat across the board, but the $200B capex plan for 2026 was the story** — it spooked markets while bulls argue it positions AWS to double revenue by 2028.\n\nSources:\n- [Amazon IR Official Release](https://ir.aboutamazon.com/news-release/news-release-details/2026/Amazon-com-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Results/)\n- [CNBC Q4 Earnings Report](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Futurum Group: AWS +24% Amid $200B Capex](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/amazon-q4-fy-2025-revenue-beat-aws-24-amid-200b-capex-plan/)\n- [Investing.com: Revenue +14%, AWS +24%](https://www.investing.com/news/company-news/amazon-q4-2025-slides-revenue-jumps-14-aws-growth-accelerates-to-24-93CH-4489269)\n- [Morningstar: $200B Capex Overshadows Results](https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/amazon-earnings-guidance-200-billion-capital-expenditure-2026-overshadows-good-results)\n- [Yahoo Finance: Stock Falls on Capex](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/amazon-stock-slides-9-2026-213833761.html)\n- [Motley Fool Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [SEC Official Filing](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1018724/000101872426000002/amzn-20251231xex991.htm)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Here is a complete summary of Amazon's Q4 2025 earnings findings:\n\n---\n\n## Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings " ;
