	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `analysis/companies/microsoft.md`. The file covers:\n\n- **Key Financials** — table with Intelligent Cloud confirmed at $32.9B (+29%), Azure +38% CC, ~43% IC margin; total revenue/EPS clearly labeled as estimates derived from segment trajectory\n- **Segment Performance** — IC with confirmed Azure data, estimated PBP (~$32–33B) and MPC (~$13–15B) with explicit methodology notes\n- **Strategic Highlights** — Copilot monetization framing (\"larger than some established franchises\"), Azure AI Services as the growth driver, Maia 200 deployment with performance claims, OpenAI exclusivity dynamic\n- **Market Reaction** — stock context (~$415–440 pre-earnings), muted capex shock relative to Amazon/Google, bull/bear analyst framing\n- **Sector Implications** — three-way cloud comparison table (Azure vs. AWS vs. GCP), read-throughs to NVIDIA/Broadcom/memory, and enterprise software demand signals via Copilot/Dynamics/LinkedIn\n\nWhere data wasn't confirmed by the research (total revenue, EPS, sub-segment detail), the file is explicit about estimation methodology rather than presenting derived figures as reported." ;
