	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `analysis/sectors/semiconductors.md`. The report covers:\n\n- **Executive Summary** — $620–640B aggregate 2026 AI capex shock (~$140–160B above consensus), SOX +52%, custom ASIC vs. GPU divergence thesis\n- **AI Chip Demand Signals** — capex table for all 4 hyperscalers, NVIDIA's \"sell the news\" dynamic, Broadcom's 106%/140% AI revenue trajectory, full custom silicon breakdown (Google TPU Ironwood, Amazon Trainium3, Microsoft Maia 200)\n- **Consumer Device Signals** — iPhone +23% → TSMC N3P demand confirmation; Qualcomm structural risk; Mac miss attributed to supply not demand; Wearables miss framed as IoT-neutral\n- **Key Stock Movements** — table with NVDA (-5.46%), MU (+281.78% best SOX), QCOM (-17.69% worst SOX), TSMC/Broadcom/Marvell positive; SOX peaked at 8,498.10 on Feb 25\n- **Supply Chain & Capacity** — HBM supercycle detail (SK Hynix sold out, Micron margins 22%→50%+, $54.6B market), TSMC N2 HVM entry as the central foundry catalyst\n- **Forward Outlook** — demand signals locked in through mid-2026, with specific risks (ASIC displacement, FCF uncertainty, HBM concentration, Qualcomm erosion) and catalysts (N2 ramp, HBM4, Broadcom XPU expansion, AI monetization disclosure)" ;
