	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `/private/tmp/swarm-parallel-stocks/analysis/correlations.md`.\n\nThe report covers all required sections with analyst-grade synthesis:\n\n- **Shared Themes** (5): Universal beats overshadowed by capex; \"supply constrained\" cross-company signal; deliberate AI revenue opacity; AWS/GCP backlog convergence at $240–244B; the Anthropic axis (Amazon + Google jointly funding the same AI lab)\n- **Key Divergences** (5): Apple as net beneficiary vs. net spender; Microsoft's gradual capex signaling vs. Amazon/Alphabet's shock announcements; cloud margin spread (43% vs. 20%); the revenue quality paradox in advertising; AI monetization timeline gaps across companies\n- **AI Arms Race**: $495–640B combined 2026 capex table; custom silicon race (TPU Ironwood/Trainium3/Maia 200) with ASIC +44.6% vs. GPU +16.1% growth projections; debt-financing analysis (Amazon's EUR 14.5B bond)\n- **Revenue Comparison**: Tables covering headline growth, cloud segments, operating margins\n- **Sector Ripple Effects**: TSMC as the universal chokepoint; HBM supercycle; SOX +52%; walled-garden ad consolidation; cloud optimization cycle absorption\n- **Investor Sentiment**: The January 29 vs. February 4–5 sentiment divergence; capex contagion mechanics; analyst consensus vs. market reaction gap\n- **Strategic Implications**: The 2027–2028 depreciation cliff, four distinct competitive postures, and why traditional competitive analysis frameworks break down when Amazon and Google jointly fund Anthropic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
