# === finding-ae7a4a55-97ba-4bec-b26a-65fca100cb99 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-ae7a4a55-97ba-4bec-b26a-65fca100cb99> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-27T17:04:19.126617Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Apple Q4 2025 earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "91ea36f6-9248-4f8f-a35c-65603e275bb8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:04:19.126457+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here are the complete findings for Apple's fiscal Q1 2026 (calendar Q4 2025) earnings:\n\n---\n\n## Apple Fiscal Q1 2026 Earnings Summary\n**Reported:** January 29, 2026 | **Quarter ended:** December 27, 2025\n\n### 1. Revenue & EPS\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | Beat | YoY |\n|--------|--------|----------|------|-----|\n| Revenue | **$143.8B** | ~$137.3B | +4.6% | +16% |\n| Diluted EPS | **$2.84** | $2.66 | +6.77% | +19% |\n| Gross Margin | **48.2%** | ~47.5% | Beat | — |\n| Net Profit | **$42.1B** | — | — | — |\n\nAll-time records across the board.\n\n### 2. Segment Revenue\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY | vs. Est. |\n|---------|---------|-----|----------|\n| **iPhone** | $85.27B | **+23%** | Beat ($78.65B est.) |\n| **Services** | $30.0B | +14% | Beat (all-time record) |\n| Mac | $8.39B | -6.7% | Miss ($8.95B est.) |\n| iPad | $8.60B | +6% | Beat |\n| Wearables/Home | $11.49B | -2% | Miss (AirPods Pro 3 supply) |\n\n### 3. Key Highlights\n- **China surged +38% YoY** to $25.53B — major upside surprise\n- Installed base exceeded **2.5 billion active devices**\n- iPhone 17 series called \"by far the most popular\" lineup ever\n\n### 4. Q2 FY2026 Guidance\n- Revenue growth: **+13% to +16%** YoY\n- Gross margin: **48%–49%**\n- Headwinds: advanced node supply constraints + rising memory costs\n\n### 5. Stock Reaction\n- **Earnings day (Jan 29):** Stock went from ~$256.44 → ~$259.48 (**+1.19%**)\n- Muted reaction despite the large beat — expectations were already elevated; stock had fallen ~9% since Jan 1\n\n### 6. Analyst Activity\n- **Raymond James** (early Jan, pre-earnings): Downgraded to Market Perform — stretched valuation, skepticism on AI catalyst\n- **Maxim Group** (Jan 30): PT raised to **$300**\n- **Evercore** (post-earnings): Reaffirmed Buy, PT **$330**\n\n---\n\nAll findings saved to memory at `/Users/renzo/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-swarm-parallel-stocks/memory/apple_q1_2026_earnings.md`.\n\nSources:\n- [Apple Newsroom – Q1 2026 Results](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [MacRumors – Record Q1 2026 Results](https://www.macrumors.com/2026/01/29/apple-1q-2026-earnings/)\n- [CNBC – Apple Q1 2026 Earnings Report](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-earnings-report-q1-2026.html)\n- [Yahoo Finance – Q1 2026 Earnings Call Highlights](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/apple-inc-aapl-q1-2026-050239886.html)\n- [Motley Fool – Q1 2026 Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-q1-2026-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [Investing.com – Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-apple-q1-2026-earnings-beat-expectations-93CH-4474928)\n- [Capital.com – Post-earnings analyst targets](https://capital.com/en-int/market-updates/apple-stock-forecast-20-02-2026)\n- [CNBC – Raymond James Downgrade](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/02/raymond-james-downgrades-apple-says-gains-will-be-hard-to-come-by-in-2026.html)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "3dc3f394-56eb-4010-b73a-36cff4b16686" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here are the complete findings for Apple's fiscal Q1 2026 (calendar Q4 2025) earnings:\n\n---\n\n## Apple Fiscal Q1 2026 Earnings Summary\n**Reported:** January 29, 2026 | **Quarter ended:** December 27, 2025\n\n### 1. Revenue & EPS\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | Beat | YoY |\n|--------|--------|----------|------|-----|\n| Revenue | **$143.8B** | ~$137.3B | +4.6% | +16% |\n| Diluted EPS | **$2.84** | $2.66 | +6.77% | +19% |\n| Gross Margin | **48.2%** | ~47.5% | Beat | — |\n| Net Profit | **$42.1B** | — | — | — |\n\nAll-time records across the board.\n\n### 2. Segment Revenue\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY | vs. Est. |\n|---------|---------|-----|----------|\n| **iPhone** | $85.27B | **+23%** | Beat ($78.65B est.) |\n| **Services** | $30.0B | +14% | Beat (all-time record) |\n| Mac | $8.39B | -6.7% | Miss ($8.95B est.) |\n| iPad | $8.60B | +6% | Beat |\n| Wearables/Home | $11.49B | -2% | Miss (AirPods Pro 3 supply) |\n\n### 3. Key Highlights\n- **China surged +38% YoY** to $25.53B — major upside surprise\n- Installed base exceeded **2.5 billion active devices**\n- iPhone 17 series called \"by far the most popular\" lineup ever\n\n### 4. Q2 FY2026 Guidance\n- Revenue growth: **+13% to +16%** YoY\n- Gross margin: **48%–49%**\n- Headwinds: advanced node supply constraints + rising memory costs\n\n### 5. Stock Reaction\n- **Earnings day (Jan 29):** Stock went from ~$256.44 → ~$259.48 (**+1.19%**)\n- Muted reaction despite the large beat — expectations were already elevated; stock had fallen ~9% since Jan 1\n\n### 6. Analyst Activity\n- **Raymond James** (early Jan, pre-earnings): Downgraded to Market Perform — stretched valuation, skepticism on AI catalyst\n- **Maxim Group** (Jan 30): PT raised to **$300**\n- **Evercore** (post-earnings): Reaffirmed Buy, PT **$330**\n\n---\n\nAll findings saved to memory at `/Users/renzo/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-swarm-parallel-stocks/memory/apple_q1_2026_earnings.md`.\n\nSources:\n- [Apple Newsroom – Q1 2026 Results](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [MacRumors – Record Q1 2026 Results](https://www.macrumors.com/2026/01/29/apple-1q-2026-earnings/)\n- [CNBC – Apple Q1 2026 Earnings Report](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-earnings-report-q1-2026.html)\n- [Yahoo Finance – Q1 2026 Earnings Call Highlights](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/apple-inc-aapl-q1-2026-050239886.html)\n- [Motley Fool – Q1 2026 Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-q1-2026-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [Investing.com – Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-apple-q1-2026-earnings-beat-expectations-93CH-4474928)\n- [Capital.com – Post-earnings analyst targets](https://capital.com/en-int/market-updates/apple-stock-forecast-20-02-2026)\n- [CNBC – Raymond James Downgrade](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/02/raymond-james-downgrades-apple-says-gains-will-be-hard-to-come-by-in-2026.html)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Here are the complete findings for Apple's fiscal Q1 2026 (calendar Q4 2025) earnings:\n\n---\n\n## Appl" ;
