# === finding-b507bc90-4043-4ae3-9de2-aee07dbaff10 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-b507bc90-4043-4ae3-9de2-aee07dbaff10> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-27T17:12:04.680263Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Write semiconductor sector report\",\"coder\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "91ea36f6-9248-4f8f-a35c-65603e275bb8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:12:04.680109+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "I need write permission to create the file. Please approve the write to either `/private/tmp/swarm-parallel-stocks/analysis/sectors/semiconductors.md` or `/tmp/swarm-parallel-stocks/analysis/sectors/semiconductors.md`.\n\nThe report is fully drafted and covers:\n\n1. **The ~$650–700B capex signal** — all four hyperscalers, what they announced, and why it matters for semiconductors\n2. **NVIDIA's paradox** — record $68.1B revenue yet -5.46% stock drop; the \"buy the rumor, sell the news\" dynamic explained\n3. **Custom silicon** — Broadcom (+106% AI revenue), Marvell, and each hyperscaler's chip (TPU Ironwood, Trainium3, Maia 200) shifting the GPU/ASIC mix\n4. **TSMC** — benefiting from AI *and* consumer electronics (Apple iPhone 17) simultaneously on the same N3/N2 nodes\n5. **Memory supercycle** — Micron +282% (best SOX performer), HBM sold out, 1990s comparison\n6. **SOX performance** — 8,498 peak, +52% 12-month return, Qualcomm as worst performer (-17.7%)\n7. **Sub-sector scorecard** and **5 key risk factors**" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "77d75fb4-58ca-4c68-96c2-c186b1fbb212" ;
