# === finding-ed00401a-027b-4caf-ab50-e3a44fc3d2b6 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-ed00401a-027b-4caf-ab50-e3a44fc3d2b6> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-27T17:06:33.557141Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Microsoft Q4 2025 earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "91ea36f6-9248-4f8f-a35c-65603e275bb8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:06:33.556942+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "File writing requires interactive approval in this permission context. All research findings are compiled and ready. Here is the complete structured summary:\n\n---\n\n## Microsoft Fiscal Q2 2026 / Calendar Q4 2025 Earnings\n**Reported:** January 28, 2026 (after market close)\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & Growth\n| Metric | Value | YoY |\n|---|---|---|\n| Total Revenue | $81.3B | +17% (+15% CC) |\n| Operating Income | $38.3B | +21% |\n| Net Income (GAAP) | $38.46B | +60%* |\n| Microsoft Cloud | $51.5B | +26% |\n\n*60% GAAP net income growth includes ~$7.6B net gains from OpenAI investments\n\n### 2. EPS vs. Estimates\n- **GAAP EPS:** $5.16 (vs. $3.23 prior year; includes $1.02 from OpenAI gains)\n- **Non-GAAP EPS:** $4.14 vs. ~$3.97 estimated → **BEAT**\n- **Commercial RPO:** $625B (+110% YoY) — massive forward backlog\n\n### 3. Intelligent Cloud Segment\n- **Revenue:** $32.9B (+29% YoY; +28% CC)\n- **Azure growth:** +39% YoY (+38% CC) — Azure annualized run rate crossed $75B\n- Q3 Azure guidance: 37–38% CC (slight deceleration signaling)\n\n### 4. Productivity & Business Processes\n- **Revenue:** $34.1B (+16% YoY; +14% CC)\n- M365 Commercial cloud: +17% YoY | M365 Consumer: +29% YoY\n- LinkedIn: +11% YoY | Dynamics 365: +19% YoY\n\n### 5. More Personal Computing\n- **Revenue:** $14.3B (−3% YoY)\n- Gaming declined; Windows OEM +1%; Search partially offset\n\n### 6. AI / Copilot Adoption\n- **M365 Copilot:** 15M paid seats; +160% seat growth YoY; DAUs up 10x YoY; conversations/user doubled\n  - Only ~3.3% penetration of 450M M365 commercial base (headroom)\n- **GitHub Copilot:** 4.7M paid subscribers (+75% YoY)\n- Nadella: *\"We are only at the beginning phases of AI diffusion and already Microsoft has built an AI business that is larger than some of our biggest franchises.\"*\n- AI WAN / \"AI super factory\" at Fairwater DCs; +50% inferencing throughput; +1 GW capacity added in Q2\n\n### 7. Capital Expenditures\n- **Q2 CapEx:** $37.5B (+66% YoY) — exceeded analyst estimate of ~$34.3B\n- ~2/3 on short-lived assets (GPUs/CPUs for AI inference)\n- H1 FY2026 total: $72.4B → tracking ~$100B annualized\n- Q3 sequential CapEx decrease expected (finance lease timing)\n\n### 8. Forward Guidance (Q3 FY2026)\n- **Revenue:** $80.65B–$81.75B (+15–17% YoY)\n- **Azure:** 37–38% growth in constant currency\n- **Cloud Gross Margin:** ~65% (down YoY due to AI infrastructure investments)\n\n### 9. Management Commentary\n- Nadella's three AI layers: \"cloud and token factory\" → \"agent platform\" → \"high-value agentic experiences\"\n- *\"Agents are the new apps\"* — positioning agents as next paradigm shift\n- Focus on \"tokens per watt per dollar\" efficiency\n- Building heterogeneous, distributed AI infrastructure\n\n### 10. Stock Price Reaction\n- **After-hours Jan 28:** −7%\n- **Jan 29 trading day:** −10%, wiping out ~$357B in market cap\n- Worst single-day decline since March 2020\n- Root concern: Azure deceleration (39% vs. prior 41%) + capex running well ahead of revenue growth\n\n### 11. Key Analyst Reactions\n- **Edward Jones (Logan Purk):** *\"Capex is growing faster than we expected, and maybe Azure is growing a little bit slower than we expected\"* — ROI timeline concern\n- **Bernstein:** Called the capex prioritization *\"a hard but necessary decision\"* and concluded *\"Microsoft's growth engine is in fact getting stronger\"*\n- **Bull case:** $625B backlog, AI monetization early innings, 10x DAU growth on Copilot\n- **Bear case:** Azure decelerating while CapEx accelerates, margin pressure from AI infrastructure\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Press Release](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/press-release-webcast)\n- [CNBC: Microsoft MSFT Q2 Earnings Report 2026](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Futurum: Microsoft Q2 FY2026 Cloud Surpasses $50B; Azure Up 38% CC](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)\n- [Yahoo Finance: Microsoft Q2 2026 Earnings Call Highlights](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-call-highlights-010010532.html)\n- [Motley Fool: MSFT Q2 2026 Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-2026-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [Microsoft Source: Cloud and AI strength drives Q2 results](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)\n- [Seeking Alpha: Microsoft Q3 guidance summary](https://seekingalpha.com/news/4543931-microsoft-outlines-80_65b-81_75b-q3-revenue-target-amid-accelerating-ai-cloud-demand-and-copilot-seat-growth)\n- [Investing.com: Earnings call transcript](https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-microsoft-q2-2026-sees-revenue-growth-stock-declines-93CH-4481140)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "f25449f8-b3e6-4e04-9f68-9452c6f15676" ;
