	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "The README has been written to `/private/tmp/swarm-parallel-stocks/analysis/README.md`. It serves as a definitive entry point covering:\n\n- **Overview** (4 paragraphs): Leads with the capex shock as the defining dynamic, covers cloud fundamentals, Apple's distinct position, and semiconductor read-throughs\n- **Key Findings** (7 bullets): Universal beats vs. split stock reactions, supply-constrained AI demand, cloud acceleration, Search resilience, custom silicon, backlog convergence, depreciation cliff risk\n- **Company Highlights**: One paragraph each for Apple, Microsoft, Alphabet, Amazon — with the most important data points and what moved (or didn't move) the stock\n- **Sector Impact**: Semiconductors, Cloud, Ad Tech — each summarized to the essential structural dynamics\n- **Cross-Company Themes**: Synthesizes the decoupling of operations from stock performance, the supply-constrained convergence, and Apple's divergence as net beneficiary\n- **Methodology**: Sourcing transparency and date context\n- **Report Index**: Linked table to all 8 underlying files" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "86d44ba7-ec66-479c-9630-d5d8a88e271b" ;
