# === memory-25f3d65c-8421-4b1e-9865-17ddb4eafae8 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-25f3d65c-8421-4b1e-9865-17ddb4eafae8> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-27T17:11:33.657753Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Write Google company summary\",\"Read Google research\",\"coder\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "coder" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "91ea36f6-9248-4f8f-a35c-65603e275bb8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:11:33.657298+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "It looks like write permissions need to be granted for the `analysis/companies/` directory. The file content is ready — here's a summary of what was prepared for `analysis/companies/google.md`:\n\n**Structure** (matching `apple.md` exactly):\n1. **Key Financials** — headline table: $113.83B revenue (+18%), $2.82 EPS (~+8% beat), $34.46B net income (+30%), first-ever $400B+ full year\n2. **Segment Performance** — full breakdown: Search $63.1B (+17% record), Cloud $17.7B (+48% fastest hyperscaler), YouTube $11.38B (+8.7% election-comp drag), Other Bets -$3.61B operating loss (Waymo SBC)\n3. **Strategic Highlights** — Gemini 750M MAUs / 8M enterprise seats, 78% serving cost reduction, TPU Ironwood (58% custom cloud AI share), Search defense vs. GenAI competitors, Waymo milestones\n4. **The Capex Story** — dedicated section since it was the market mover: $175–185B 2026 guide vs. $119.5B expected (+$55–65B shock), FCF compression analysis\n5. **Market Reaction** — ~$343 pre-earnings → -7% to -10% the following week (~$302–$313)\n6. **Analyst Consensus** — 60 Buy / 7 Hold / 0 Sell, Goldman/RBC/Scotiabank at $400, JPM at $395, median ~$380–$387\n7. **Q1 2026 Guidance** — directional signals (no hard numbers disclosed)\n8. **Sector Implications** — cloud competitive dynamics, semiconductor read-throughs, ad market health, Waymo AV sector signal\n\nCould you approve the write permission so the file can be saved?" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "bba9ebc9-764a-4f38-8952-7f74d30138f6" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It looks like write permissions need to be granted for the `analysis/companies/` directory. The file content is ready — here's a summary of what was prepared for `analysis/companies/google.md`:\n\n**Structure** (matching `apple.md` exactly):\n1. **Key Financials** — headline table: $113.83B revenue (+18%), $2.82 EPS (~+8% beat), $34.46B net income (+30%), first-ever $400B+ full year\n2. **Segment Performance** — full breakdown: Search $63.1B (+17% record), Cloud $17.7B (+48% fastest hyperscaler), YouTube $11.38B (+8.7% election-comp drag), Other Bets -$3.61B operating loss (Waymo SBC)\n3. **Strategic Highlights** — Gemini 750M MAUs / 8M enterprise seats, 78% serving cost reduction, TPU Ironwood (58% custom cloud AI share), Search defense vs. GenAI competitors, Waymo milestones\n4. **The Capex Story** — dedicated section since it was the market mover: $175–185B 2026 guide vs. $119.5B expected (+$55–65B shock), FCF compression analysis\n5. **Market Reaction** — ~$343 pre-earnings → -7% to -10% the following week (~$302–$313)\n6. **Analyst Consensus** — 60 Buy / 7 Hold / 0 Sell, Goldman/RBC/Scotiabank at $400, JPM at $395, median ~$380–$387\n7. **Q1 2026 Guidance** — directional signals (no hard numbers disclosed)\n8. **Sector Implications** — cloud competitive dynamics, semiconductor read-throughs, ad market health, Waymo AV sector signal\n\nCould you approve the write permission so the file can be saved?" ;
