	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:15:44.593834+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `analysis/sectors/cloud.md`. The report covers:\n\n- **Market Share Dynamics** — Q4 2025 revenue table (AWS $35.6B/+24%, Azure $32.9B/+29%, GCP $17.7B/+48%), share shift analysis showing Google gaining fastest and AWS losing share\n- **AI-Driven Cloud Growth** — per-provider AI commentary with specific disclosures (Bedrock \"multibillion-dollar run rates\", Azure OpenAI 65%+ of Fortune 500, Gemini 78% serving cost reduction), plus a platform comparison table for Bedrock vs Azure OpenAI vs Vertex AI\n- **Enterprise Spending Trends** — optimization cycle declared absorbed (AWS backlog +22% QoQ as evidence), multi-cloud normalization data (85%+ enterprises multi-cloud), migration pace signals\n- **Margin Analysis** — AWS ~35% (expanding), Azure ~43% (structural premium), Google Cloud ~20% (85% YoY income growth / profitability inflection), plus the FCF/capex overhang table ($495–505B combined 2026 commitment)\n- **Cloud Ecosystem Impact** — Snowflake +44.6%, Cloudflare +20%+/+32% revenue, CrowdStrike +39.4%, MongoDB/Datadog signals, SaaS bundling risk from Microsoft Copilot\n- **Forward Outlook** — per-provider 2026 growth projections and five competitive dynamics (custom silicon, AI revenue disclosure, pricing, power constraints, regulatory)\n- **Investment Framework** — bull/bear cases and provider ranking (AWS > GCP > Azure on risk-adjusted basis)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "f9508f6f-854c-4430-a66d-72b03d994b4e" ;
