	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:12:51.149255+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written to `analysis/companies/google.md`. The file follows the same structure and tone as `apple.md`, covering:\n\n- **Key Financials** — headline table with $113.83B revenue (+18%), $2.82 EPS (~+8% beat), $34.46B net income (+30%), first-ever $400B+ full year\n- **Segment Performance** — full breakdown: Search $63.1B (+17% record), Cloud $17.7B (+48% fastest hyperscaler), YouTube $11.38B (+8.7% election-comp drag), Other Bets -$3.61B operating loss (Waymo SBC)\n- **Strategic Highlights** — Gemini 750M MAUs / 8M enterprise seats, 78% serving cost reduction, TPU Ironwood, Search AI Overviews monetization defense, Waymo milestones\n- **Market Reaction** — ~$343 pre-earnings → -7% to -10% the following week on capex shock; 60 Buy / 7 Hold / 0 Sell, targets $380–$400\n- **Sector Implications** — ad market health, Cloud share gains vs. AWS/Azure, AI infrastructure demand read-throughs (TSMC, Nvidia, networking), AV competitive benchmarking" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "84e1b2a6-6787-48de-a32c-47ac6ff6efd0" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Written to `analysis/companies/google.md`. The file follows the same structure and tone as `apple.md`, covering:\n\n- **Key Financials** — headline table with $113.83B revenue (+18%), $2.82 EPS (~+8% beat), $34.46B net income (+30%), first-ever $400B+ full year\n- **Segment Performance** — full breakdown: Search $63.1B (+17% record), Cloud $17.7B (+48% fastest hyperscaler), YouTube $11.38B (+8.7% election-comp drag), Other Bets -$3.61B operating loss (Waymo SBC)\n- **Strategic Highlights** — Gemini 750M MAUs / 8M enterprise seats, 78% serving cost reduction, TPU Ironwood, Search AI Overviews monetization defense, Waymo milestones\n- **Market Reaction** — ~$343 pre-earnings → -7% to -10% the following week on capex shock; 60 Buy / 7 Hold / 0 Sell, targets $380–$400\n- **Sector Implications** — ad market health, Cloud share gains vs. AWS/Azure, AI infrastructure demand read-throughs (TSMC, Nvidia, networking), AV competitive benchmarking" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[coder] Written to `analysis/companies/google.md`. The file follows the same structure a" ;
