	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Written `analysis/sectors/ad-tech.md`. The report covers all required sections with specific data points from the prior findings:\n\n- **Search**: Google Search $63.1B (+17%), AI Overviews additive thesis with mechanistic explanation\n- **Video/Social**: YouTube $11.38B (+8.7%), election-comp context, CTV dynamics, Meta/Snap/TikTok signals\n- **Retail Media**: Amazon $21.3B (+23%), closed-loop attribution moat, Prime Video CTV, TTD/Criteo implications\n- **AI in Advertising**: Performance Max, Advantage+, Amazon bid models, CAPI/privacy-preserving infra\n- **Holiday Quarter**: Beat table across all segments, advertiser spending pattern analysis\n- **Ecosystem Impact**: Walled garden vs. open-web structural divergence, stock reactions table (GOOG/AMZN capex shock context)\n- **Outlook**: 2026 projections table, five key risks (AI search disruption, cookie deprecation, DOJ antitrust, TikTok, CPM cycle), bull/bear cases, stocks summary table\n\nFormat mirrors `cloud.md` exactly — same table style, section depth, footnote attribution, and professional analyst tone." ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "9472ebf4-605d-4a95-8126-115cf0da2366" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Written `analysis/sectors/ad-tech.md`. The report covers all required sections with specific data points from the prior findings:\n\n- **Search**: Google Search $63.1B (+17%), AI Overviews additive thesis with mechanistic explanation\n- **Video/Social**: YouTube $11.38B (+8.7%), election-comp context, CTV dynamics, Meta/Snap/TikTok signals\n- **Retail Media**: Amazon $21.3B (+23%), closed-loop attribution moat, Prime Video CTV, TTD/Criteo implications\n- **AI in Advertising**: Performance Max, Advantage+, Amazon bid models, CAPI/privacy-preserving infra\n- **Holiday Quarter**: Beat table across all segments, advertiser spending pattern analysis\n- **Ecosystem Impact**: Walled garden vs. open-web structural divergence, stock reactions table (GOOG/AMZN capex shock context)\n- **Outlook**: 2026 projections table, five key risks (AI search disruption, cookie deprecation, DOJ antitrust, TikTok, CPM cycle), bull/bear cases, stocks summary table\n\nFormat mirrors `cloud.md` exactly — same table style, section depth, footnote attribution, and professional analyst tone." ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[coder] Written `analysis/sectors/ad-tech.md`. The report covers all required sections w" ;
