# === memory-f1e51705-dba1-449d-8f44-4a4182aadf81 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-f1e51705-dba1-449d-8f44-4a4182aadf81> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-27T17:05:57.678688Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Write Amazon company summary\",\"Read Amazon research\",\"coder\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "coder" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "91ea36f6-9248-4f8f-a35c-65603e275bb8" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-27T17:05:57.678291+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "It seems write permissions are being blocked. The Amazon Q4 2025 earnings summary is ready to write — here's the full content that should go into `analysis/companies/amazon.md`:\n\n---\n\n# Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Summary\n\n**Reported:** February 5, 2026 | **Quarter ended:** December 31, 2025\n\n---\n\n## Financial Highlights\n\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | Result | YoY |\n|--------|--------|----------|--------|-----|\n| Total Revenue | **$213.4B** | $211.3B | Beat | +14% |\n| Diluted EPS | **$1.95** | $1.97 | Slight miss | — |\n| AWS Revenue | **$35.6B** | $34.9B | Beat | +24% |\n| Advertising Revenue | **$21.3B** | — | — | +23% |\n\n---\n\n## Segment Revenue\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY |\n|---------|---------|-----|\n| **North America** | $127.1B | +10% |\n| **International** | $50.7B | +17% (+11% constant currency) |\n| **AWS** | $35.6B | +24% |\n\n---\n\n## AWS Deep Dive\n\n- Fastest growth in **13 quarters**; annualized run rate ~$142B\n- **Operating income:** $12.47B (beat $11.91B estimate)\n- **Operating margin:** ~35% (up from 34.6% in Q3 2025)\n- **Order backlog:** $244B (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ)\n\n---\n\n## AI & Infrastructure\n\n- **Bedrock** adopted by 100,000+ companies\n- **Trainium2:** 1.4M chips deployed, fully subscribed; powers Project Rainier\n- **Trainium + Graviton** combined ARR: $10B+, triple-digit YoY growth\n- **Trainium3:** In production; nearly all supply committed by mid-2026\n- **Trainium4:** Expected 2027 — 6x FP4 compute vs. Trainium3\n\n---\n\n## Capital Expenditure\n\n- **2026 CapEx: ~$200B** vs. analyst estimate of $146.6B (+56% shock)\n- Focus: AI infrastructure, custom silicon, robotics, Project Kuiper satellites\n\n---\n\n## Q1 2026 Guidance\n\n- Revenue: **$173.5B–$178.5B** (in-line with $175.2B estimate)\n- Operating income: **$16.5B–$21.5B**\n- ~180 bps FX tailwind\n\n---\n\n## Stock Reaction\n\n- After-hours: **-11%** | Next day: **-8%** | Weeks later: still ~15% below pre-announcement\n- Cause: $200B capex shock overshadowed all operational beats\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n1. **AWS reaccelerating** — 24% is the fastest growth in 13 quarters\n2. **Advertising as second engine** — $21.3B at +23% approaching Google-scale\n3. **AI capex is the central debate** — $200B signals full commitment to AI infrastructure leadership\n4. **EPS miss was marginal** — $1.95 vs. $1.97 is noise vs. the AWS beat\n5. **International inflecting** — +17% YoY with FX tailwind\n\n---\n\nPlease approve the write permission so I can save this to `analysis/companies/amazon.md`. The file is ready to go." ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "fa4f1f19-e4f5-43d1-b64b-aa1dfdd71b78" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It seems write permissions are being blocked. The Amazon Q4 2025 earnings summary is ready to write — here's the full content that should go into `analysis/companies/amazon.md`:\n\n---\n\n# Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Summary\n\n**Reported:** February 5, 2026 | **Quarter ended:** December 31, 2025\n\n---\n\n## Financial Highlights\n\n| Metric | Actual | Estimate | Result | YoY |\n|--------|--------|----------|--------|-----|\n| Total Revenue | **$213.4B** | $211.3B | Beat | +14% |\n| Diluted EPS | **$1.95** | $1.97 | Slight miss | — |\n| AWS Revenue | **$35.6B** | $34.9B | Beat | +24% |\n| Advertising Revenue | **$21.3B** | — | — | +23% |\n\n---\n\n## Segment Revenue\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY |\n|---------|---------|-----|\n| **North America** | $127.1B | +10% |\n| **International** | $50.7B | +17% (+11% constant currency) |\n| **AWS** | $35.6B | +24% |\n\n---\n\n## AWS Deep Dive\n\n- Fastest growth in **13 quarters**; annualized run rate ~$142B\n- **Operating income:** $12.47B (beat $11.91B estimate)\n- **Operating margin:** ~35% (up from 34.6% in Q3 2025)\n- **Order backlog:** $244B (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ)\n\n---\n\n## AI & Infrastructure\n\n- **Bedrock** adopted by 100,000+ companies\n- **Trainium2:** 1.4M chips deployed, fully subscribed; powers Project Rainier\n- **Trainium + Graviton** combined ARR: $10B+, triple-digit YoY growth\n- **Trainium3:** In production; nearly all supply committed by mid-2026\n- **Trainium4:** Expected 2027 — 6x FP4 compute vs. Trainium3\n\n---\n\n## Capital Expenditure\n\n- **2026 CapEx: ~$200B** vs. analyst estimate of $146.6B (+56% shock)\n- Focus: AI infrastructure, custom silicon, robotics, Project Kuiper satellites\n\n---\n\n## Q1 2026 Guidance\n\n- Revenue: **$173.5B–$178.5B** (in-line with $175.2B estimate)\n- Operating income: **$16.5B–$21.5B**\n- ~180 bps FX tailwind\n\n---\n\n## Stock Reaction\n\n- After-hours: **-11%** | Next day: **-8%** | Weeks later: still ~15% below pre-announcement\n- Cause: $200B capex shock overshadowed all operational beats\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n1. **AWS reaccelerating** — 24% is the fastest growth in 13 quarters\n2. **Advertising as second engine** — $21.3B at +23% approaching Google-scale\n3. **AI capex is the central debate** — $200B signals full commitment to AI infrastructure leadership\n4. **EPS miss was marginal** — $1.95 vs. $1.97 is noise vs. the AWS beat\n5. **International inflecting** — +17% YoY with FX tailwind\n\n---\n\nPlease approve the write permission so I can save this to `analysis/companies/amazon.md`. The file is ready to go." ;
